From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] Override async methods to avoid sync-over-async

Bottleneck #2: The public ExecuteQuery() and ExecuteUpdate() methods
wrap async implementations with .GetAwaiter().GetResult(), which blocks
the calling thread. The base class AdbcStatement provides virtual async
methods (ExecuteQueryAsync, ExecuteUpdateAsync) whose defaults wrap the
sync methods in Task.Run — creating double wrapping.

This patch overrides ExecuteQueryAsync and ExecuteUpdateAsync to call
the internal async implementations directly, eliminating the sync-over-
async penalty for callers using the async API (e.g., Power BI async
data loading).

The sync overrides are preserved unchanged for backward compatibility
with callers using the synchronous API.

